HEADWORD: Lowboy
<hw>Low"boy`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A chest of drawers
not more than four feet high; -- applied commonly to the lower half of a
tallboy from which the upper half has been removed.</def> <mark>[U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

